Reading English can be fun, but sometimes you might find words you don&#039;t know. Don&#039;t worry, there&#039;s a secret weapon to help you! These are called &quot;*transparent* words.&quot;
Imagine you *speak* Spanish. Did you know some English words look similar to Spanish words and have the same *meaning*? For example, &quot;important&quot; in English is &quot;importante&quot; in Spanish! They both mean *significant*. Cool, right?
By recognizing these &quot;transparent words,&quot; you can unlock the meaning of new words without needing a *dictionary* every time. So, next time you&#039;re *reading*, look for *familiar* shapes in the words and see if they connect to words you already know!
